We start by choosing the relevant items from the provided statements and then use the following formulas:

1. Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
 • From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities is given by Total Current Liabilities = 2,736,025.72 and Total Owner's Equity = 11,330,150.23.  
 • Calculation: 2,736,025.72 / 11,330,150.23 ≈ 0.2413 → ≈0.24

2. Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
 • From the income statement, Net Profit = –1,669,849.77 and Total Revenue = 6,920,513.79.  
 • Calculation: (–1,669,849.77 / 6,920,513.79) × 100% ≈ –24.13%

3. Return on Assets (ROA) = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%  
 • From the balance sheet, Total Assets = 14,066,175.95.  
 • Calculation: (–1,669,849.77 / 14,066,175.95) × 100% ≈ –11.87%

4. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
 • Accounts Receivable at the beginning is 0 and at the end is 2,923,459.19, so the average is (0 + 2,923,459.19) / 2 = 1,461,729.595.  
 • Calculation: 6,920,513.79 / 1,461,729.595 ≈ 4.73

Thus, our final answers in the required JSON format are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.24",
    "Net Profit Margin": "-24.13%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "-11.87%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "4.73"
  }
}
